man Syria and the Near East|first=Kevin|last=Butcher|publisher=The British Museum Press|year=2003|isbn=978-0-7141-2235-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Byli\u0144ski|first=Janusz|year= 1995|title=Palmyra: Arab Castle|journal=Polish Archaeology in the Mediterranean|publisher=Warsaw University Press|volume=7|editor1-first=Micha\u0142|editor1-last=Gawlikowski|editor2-first=Wiktor A.|editor2-last=Daszewski|issn= 1234-5415|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|first=Janusz|last=Byli\u0144ski|year=1999|title=Qal'at Shirkuh at Palmyra: A Medieval Fortress Reinterpreted|journal=Bulletin d'\u00c9tudes Orientales|publisher=l'Institut fran\u00e7ais d'arch\u00e9ologie du Proche-Orient|volume=51|issn=2077-4079|isbn=978-2-901315-56-8|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Christina|last1=Cameron|first2=Mechtild|last2=R\u00f6ssler|title=Many Voices, One Vision: The Early Years of the World Heritage Convention|origyear=2013|year= 2016|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-10102-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|last=Carissimo|first=Justin|publisher=The Independent|date= 4 July 2015|title=Isis propaganda video shows 25 Syrian soldiers executed by teenage militants in Palmyra|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/isis-propaganda-video-shows-20-syrian-government-soldiers-executed-in-palmyra-by-young-islamists-10366533.html|accessdate=4 March 2017|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Syria & Lebanon|first1=Terry |last1=Carter|first2=Lara|last2= Dunston|first3=Amelia |last3=Thomas|publisher=Lonely Planet|year=2008|isbn=978-1-74104-609-0|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=Francesca|last=Casule|translator1-first=Paula Elise|translator1-last=Boomsliter|translator2-first=Richard|translator2-last=Dunbar|title=Art and History: Syria|year= 2008|publisher=Casa Editrice Bonechi|isbn=978-88-476-0119-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Battle Honours of the Second World War 1939\u20131945 and Korea 1950\u20131953: British and Colonial Regiments|first1=Terry |last1=Cave|origyear=2003|publisher=Andrews UK Li